V.CONCLUSION
In the above we have investigated the transient
effects of SEIR-models when initializing the system
away from the dominant eigenvector and the conse-
quences for the observed growth rate.
As expected,an outbreak starting in the more ac-
tive groups converges faster,and the same is true for
amore infectiousdisease.The significant part is the
time scale on which the convergence occurs.It turns
out that,usingrealistic parameters,the growth rate
hasconverged within three weeks,which also means
that it is safe to estimate it at this point.
